docs.lead_paragraph: GUAYAQUIL, Jan. 30. -- The reaction in local commercial circles to the Japanese trade mission which visited this city recently indicated that Japan cannot expect to sell to Ecuador without buying here or paying special import duties on its own low-priced goods sold here.

docs.snippet: BUENOS AIRES, Feb. 4. -- Argentina has begun an exclusion of European nations from the benefits of South American trade agreements which might lead eventually to the realization of Chile's proposed South American customs union. This is in accordance...
docs.lead_paragraph: BUENOS AIRES, Feb. 4. -- Argentina has begun an exclusion of European nations from the benefits of South American trade agreements which might lead eventually to the realization of Chile's proposed South American customs union. This is in accordance with a principle that several South American republics tried repeatedly but without success to have adopted by the Pan-American Conference at Montevideo.
docs.abstract: New agreement; exclusion of Eur nations from benefits of South Amer agreements begun by Argentina

docs.lead_paragraph: TWO trunk stand in all office of the State Department, unlocked but not yet unpacked, splashed with London labels which have been almost obscured by brilliant pasters from Montevideo. Bulging with books and papers, they testify to the travel habits of the most peripatetic Secretary of State this country has ever known.
